ðŸ”¹ Project Overview

This project explores a banking marketing dataset to understand customer behavior and identify factors that influence whether a client subscribes to a term deposit. The goal is to use data analysis and machine learning to improve decision-making in marketing campaigns.

ðŸ”¹ Objectives

Analyze customer demographics and behavior.

Identify key factors that influence campaign success.

Build predictive models to classify potential customers.

Provide actionable insights for better marketing strategies.

ðŸ”¹ Tools & Skills Used

Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn)

Machine Learning (Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forests)

Data Visualization for insights and storytelling

ðŸ”¹ Key Insights

Certain age groups and occupations showed higher conversion rates.

Contact method and campaign frequency strongly impacted outcomes.

Machine learning models provided a way to predict potential subscribers with good accuracy.

ðŸ”¹ Results

The predictive model helps banks target the right customers, reduce marketing costs, and improve overall campaign effectiveness.

ðŸ”¹ Next Steps

Test advanced models (XGBoost, Neural Networks).

Deploy the model into a dashboard for real-time campaign support.
